<!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════ -->
<h2>Kanaha Bathymetry</h2>

<p>Kanaha's reef creates both opportunity (wave breaking for surf) and hazard (mast/foil strike). Understanding the depth profile is essential for safe equipment selection.</p>

<h3>Shore to Old Mans Reef</h3>
<p>Old Mans reef sits approximately 200-300m offshore at Kanaha. At mean lower low water (MLLW), the reef is approximately <strong>0.9m deep</strong>. Tides add to this baseline:</p>

<pre><code>reef_depth = 0.9m + (tide_ft × 0.3048)</code></pre>

<h3>Mast Selection Logic</h3>

