<h3>Why Longer Period = Faster Travel + More Predictable</h3>
<p>Swell energy travels at group velocity, which is directly proportional to wave period:</p>
<pre><code>Cg = g × T / (4π)   m/s</code></pre>
<p>This means:</p>
<ul>
  <li>A <strong>16-second swell</strong> travels at ~12.5 m/s (24 kts) — arrives quickly</li>
  <li>An <strong>8-second swell</strong> travels at ~6.2 m/s (12 kts) — takes twice as long</li>
  <li>Longer period also means the swell has traveled farther, which means it's more organized (short-period chop has already dissipated)</li>
</ul>

